args: All right. I think that's everything we\nneed for today's shopping.
Shall we head back to the Halidom?
Uh, guys? Don't wanna alarm nobody,\nbut there's someone runnin' pell-mell\nright at us.
Er, sorry. Can you maybe slow down and\ntry that again?
Right! Of course. Sorry about that. *ahem*\nGood sir! Might you know anything about\nthe legendary frozen city?
The frozen city is a faerie tale.
Sure is! And I'm looking for it.
But you just agreed with me that it is a\nfaerie tale?
Yeah, I know. But I ALSO think it might\nactually exist somewhere in the world.
Anyway, that's why I've been running all\nover the place asking folks if they know\nanything and gathering info and the like.
Hmm. I would attempt to keep your\nhopes firmly in check on this matter.
Fair enough. Oh, and sorry for getting all\nup in your grill like that.
I don't know that I'm familiar with a story\nabout a frozen city.
It's about an adventurer who stumbles into\na city where all the buildings are hewn\nfrom solid ice.
Hey, I remember that one! That explorer\ncat eventually found an ice palace with a\nhot princess inside it, yeah?

Crudely put, but essentially correct.
Anyway, the tale ends with the adventurer
returning home to find their own
hometown completely frozen over.
Just your typical faerie tale, really.
But this city doesn't actually exist in\nreality, right?
The world is vast, so I suppose we can't\ndeny it for certain.
Aw, c'mon. It ain't real. No WAY it's real!\nThat guy what's lookin' for it is just a few\nturkey legs short of a dinner buffet.
Hey there, friend! Do you know anything\nabout the frozen city?
Can do! Thanks for your help.\n...Hey there! Excuse me!
Damn, he's still goin' at it. Any normal\nperson woulda gotten discouraged and\ngiven up by now.
That kind of perseverance is actually a\nrather admirable quality.
If applied correctly, perhaps.\n...Hmm? What's going on now?
Oy, mister! Yer lookin' for the frozen city\nwhat never melts, yeah?
I sure am! Do you know anything?
Actually, I gots me hands on some'a the\nNevermelt Ice what that frozen city is\nmade from.
WHAAAAT?! Um, I mean...do you think I\nmight take a look at it?
Ah ah aaaah! This here ice is real trig,\nyeah? Can't just be lettin' any old fool\nset his peepers on it for free.
Buuut...I might be convinced to sell it\nto yaâ€”seein' as how ya seems like a\nreal stand-up fellow.
As for the price, what say you and me\nsettle on...this much?
Holy wow! That's...a lot.\nLike, a LOT a lot.
This here's the rarest of the rare, so it is!\nCan't let it go for a song, now can I?
Hmm, I suppose that's true. All right then,\nyou have a deal!
Pleasure doin' business with ya.\nEnjoy yer ice! *snicker*
Well, there's nothing at all suspicious\nabout that transaction.
That guy might be a dope, but I ain't gonna\nstand around and let him get fleeced.\n...Hey, buddy! Hold up!
Couldn't help but overhear what just went\ndown. Mind if I take a peek at that\nNevermelt Ice ya just picked up?
Ha! I KNEW you were interested!\nBy all means, have a look.
I'm afraid this isn't ice at all. It's glass.
'Fraid so. Hang onâ€”I'll go get yer money\nback from that swindler.
Er, you don't have to do that. To be honest,\nI actually had my suspicions when I made\nthe purchase.
Then why did you do it?
Well, what if it WAS real?
That's hardly a logical thought process.
If there's a chance, you have to try!\nThat's adventure!
You never know if you're dealing with\ntruth or fictionâ€”that's why you go on\nthe adventure in the first place!
Besides, even if you fail, there's no harm\ndone to anyone, yeah?
You are a very strange man.
Bwa ha ha! I love this guy! He knows just\nwhat to say to fire me up!
Then you understand what I'm getting at?\nOh, this is just GREAT!
Look, I'd love to help ya out here, but I\njust ain't sure about this whole ï¼‚frozen\ncityï¼‚ business.
We've been to a lot of different places,\nbut I haven't heard a word about a city\nmade from ice in any of them.
You've been to a lot of different places?\nWho the heck ARE you guys?
...Anyway, that's about the long and short\nof it.
You...guys...are...AMAAAZING!\nCan I come with you? Pleeeease?!
Heh. Normally we have to dance around\na little more before we recruit folks.
You've touched me deep in my adventure-\nloving heart. Please let me help you out\nhowever I can!
Also, if I'm with you, I'll be able to have\nexperiences in all SORTS of places!
I'm always open to new companions.\nPlus, I like his sunny outlook on things!
Thank you! I'm Pietro the adventurer,\nand I can't wait to see where our\njourneys together will take us!
